text: Emilee Wallace (born September 19, 1989) is an American actress. ==Career== Wallace began her acting career in 2005. She has appeared in episodes of the television series Judging Amy (2005), Grey's Anatomy (2006), Cold Case (2008), Boston Legal (2008), Glee (2009, 2013), Ghost Whisperer (2010), Workaholics (2012), Rizzoli & Isles (2012-present). Apart from television work, she also appeared on the television movies Company Town (2006) and Amish Grace (2010), and her first feature movie Balls Out: Gary the Tennis Coach (2008). ==Filmography== ===Television=== Year TV series Role Episode count 2005 Judging Amy Regan Swope 1 episode 2006 Grey's Anatomy Amelia Carver 1 episode 2008 Cold Case Tamyra Borden (1998) 1 episode 2008 Boston Legal Fiona 1 episode 2009, 2013 Glee Deaf choir 2 episodes 2010 Ghost Whisperer TJ 1 episode 2012 Workaholics Whitney 1 episode 2012-present Rizzoli & Isles Cailin Martin 4 episodes ===Other=== Year Title Role Type 2006 Company Town Ronni Amberson TV movie 2008 Balls Out: Gary the Tennis Coach Jenny Tuttle Feature movie 2010 Amish Grace Teacher Ruth TV movie ==Personal life== Wallace was born in Oklahoma City and raised in Edmond, Oklahoma. Her brother, BJ (born 1991), is also an actor. She went to California State University (CSU) and now lives in Los Angeles, California. ==References== ==Other websites== * * * Category:1989 births Category:Actors from Oklahoma City Category:American movie actors Category:American television actors Category:Living people
